# Clean up data and merge to one dataframe
new_df = pd.merge(pitches, atbats,  how='left', left_on='ab_id', right_on = 'ab_id')

new_df1 = pd.merge(new_df, games,  how='left', left_on='g_id', right_on = 'g_id')

new_df2 = pd.merge(new_df1, player_name,  how='left', left_on='batter_id', right_on = 'batter_id')
new_df2['Batters Name'] = new_df2[['first_name', 'last_name']].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x), axis=1)
new_df2.drop(['first_name', 'last_name'], axis=1, inplace=True)

player_name.rename(columns={'batter_id': 'pitcher_id'}, inplace=True)

final_df = pd.merge(new_df2, player_name,  how='left', left_on='pitcher_id', right_on = 'pitcher_id')

# apply mapping to make data more interpretable
final_df['pitch_type'] = final_df['pitch_type'].map({'FF': 'Four Seam Fastball', 'SL': 'Slider', 'FT': 'Two seam fastball', 'CH': 'Changeup', 'SI': 'Sinker', 'CU': 'Curveball', 'FC': 'Cutter', 'KC': 'Knuckle Curve', 'FS': 'Splitter','KN': 'Knuckleball', 'EP': 'Eephus', 'FO': 'Pitch Out', 'PO': 'Pitch Out', 'SC': 'Screwball', 'UN': 'Unidentified', 'FA': 'Fastball', 'IN': 'Intentional Ball'})
final_df['code'] = final_df['code'].map({'B': 'Ball', '*B': 'Ball in dirt', 'S': 'Swinging Strike', 'C': 'Called Strike', 'F': 'Foul', 'T': 'Foul Tip', 'L': 'Foul Bunt', 'I': 'Intentional Ball', 'W': 'Blocked','M': 'Missed Bunt', 'P': 'Pitch Out', 'Q': 'Swinging Pitch Out', 'R': 'Foul Pitch Out', 'X': 'In play out(s)', 'D': 'In play no out', 'E': 'In play runs'})
In [9]:
# calculate ERAs (Earned Run Average and BAs (batting averages))
grp = final_df.groupby(['Pitchers Name'])[["s_count"]].sum()
grp1 = final_df.groupby(['Batters Name'])[["b_count"]].sum()

ERA = grp.s_count / len (final_df)
BA = grp1.b_count / len (final_df) * 100

In [19]:
# Create a mapping dictionary to categorize outcomes
code_mapping = {
    'Ball': ['Ball', 'Ball in dirt', 'Blocked'],
    'Called Strike': ['Called Strike'],
    'In Play': ['In play no out', 'In play out(s)', 'In play no out', 'In play runs'],
    'Uncalled Strike': ['Swinging Strike', 'Missed Bunt', 'Foul Tip', 'Foul Bunt', 'Foul']
    # Uncalled strikes are anything where the batter swung and the ball was not in play
    # I didn't know what else to call it tbh
}
In [20]:
# Map the 'code' column to broader categories
blake_snell['outcome_category'] = blake_snell['code'].map(lambda x: next((k for k, v in code_mapping.items() if x in v), x))
# Drop rows with nan values in the 'outcome_category' column
blake_snell = blake_snell.dropna(subset=['outcome_category'])
In [23]:
# Group data by umpire and pitch outcome
umpire_stats = blake_snell.groupby(['umpire_HP', 'outcome_category']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Calculate the percentage of called strikes for each umpire
umpire_stats['Called Strike Percentage'] = umpire_stats['Called Strike'] / (umpire_stats['Called Strike'] + umpire_stats['Ball'])

umpire_stats_sorted = umpire_stats.sort_values(by='Called Strike Percentage')

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=umpire_stats_sorted.index, y='Called Strike Percentage', data=umpire_stats_sorted.reset_index())
plt.title(f"Called Strike Percentage vs. Umpire for Blake Snell")
plt.xlabel("Umpire")
plt.ylabel("Strike Percentage")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.show()
In [24]:
# Calculate the percentage of total strikes for each umpire
umpire_stats['Total Strike Percentage'] = (umpire_stats['Called Strike'] + umpire_stats['Uncalled Strike']) / (umpire_stats['Called Strike'] + umpire_stats['Uncalled Strike'] + umpire_stats['Ball'])

umpire_stats_sorted = umpire_stats.sort_values(by='Total Strike Percentage')

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=umpire_stats_sorted.index, y='Total Strike Percentage', data=umpire_stats_sorted.reset_index())
plt.title(f"Total Strike Percentage vs. Umpire for Blake Snell")
plt.xlabel("Umpire")
plt.ylabel("Total Strike Percentage")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.show()
In [25]:
pitch_outcome_heatmap = pd.crosstab(blake_snell['umpire_HP'], blake_snell['outcome_category'])

# Normalize each row to represent probabilities
normalized_pitch_outcomes = pitch_outcome_heatmap.div(pitch_outcome_heatmap.sum(axis=1), axis=0)

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 14))
sns.heatmap(normalized_pitch_outcomes, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='.2f')
plt.title("Heatmap of Pitch Outcomes by Umpire for Blake Snell")
plt.xlabel("Outcome Category")
plt.ylabel("Umpire")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.show()

An interesting trend from the heatmap... called strikes seem to be fairly consistent across umpires. Based on the other stats, I would assume that this is controlled by batters choosing to swing at strike-esque balls.

import random
def random_colors(number_of_colors):
    color = ["#"+''.join([random.choice('0123456789ABCDEF') for j in range(6)])
                 for i in range(number_of_colors)]
    return color
